<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-04-26T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-04-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1397.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-27T10:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1913; 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Quintuple reorganization loan signed this morning over protest of certain
                            senators who claim that approval by the Assembly is necessary and who
                            threaten to boycott the banks.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>